    HEADLINE
    ────────
    Morris Whisky Finishes Single Malt in Rutherglen Tokay Casks

    ANGLE
    ─────
    Morris Whisky in Rutherglen is a fortified-wine house turned single malt producer, and its competitive edge is literally in the wood: head distiller Darren Peck finishes Australian single malt in the estate's own Rutherglen fortified casks, tokay among them. The result is a whisky that can't be replicated by anyone buying cooperage off-shelf — a story about provenance, family continuity since 1859, and what happens when six generations of fortified knowledge get pointed at a still.

