    EDITORIAL FRAMING
    ─────────────────
    Lead with the barrel — the single most defensible claim Morris owns. Most Australian single malt finishes in ex-bourbon, ex-sherry, or wine casks bought from elsewhere; Morris is finishing in casks that held its own fortifieds, made on the same estate, from a lineage running back to 1859. That's the lede. Suggested structure: open in the cooperage or cellar door with a sensory hook (the tokay-finished pour in the glass), pivot to Darren Peck and the six-generation fortified backbone that makes the whisky program possible, then close on the cellar door experience and the Halliday recognition as external validation. Voice: considered, specific, restrained — let the provenance do the boasting. Avoid hagiography; the facts are strong enough without it.

